  "Allegations" : "NASD RULE 2110: WILLARD MADE MATERIAL WRITTEN MISREPRESENTATIONS TO HIS MEMBER FIRM IN CONNECTION WITH PURCHASES OF A $2 MILLION VARIABLE UNIVERSAL LIFE INSURANCE POLICY (VUL) AND A $6 MILLION VUL POLICY. ON OR ABOUT JULY 27, 2006, WILLARD SUBMITTED AN APPLICATION TO THE FIRM TO EFFECT THE PURCHASE OF A $2 MILLION VUL POLICY FOR A CUSTOMER. IN A COVER LETTER ACCOMPANYING THE APPLICATION, WILLARD WROTE, \"THE PURPOSE OF THE INSURANCE IS TO SETUP A PERMANENT LIFE INSURANCE POLICY TO PROTECT THE ESTATE OF THE CUSTOMER WHO HAS RECENTLY INHERITED $2,500,000 AND WANTS TO PROTECT IT FROM TAXES FOR HER HEIRS.\" WILLARD'S STATEMENT IN THE COVER LETTER WAS FALSE IN THAT THE CUSTOMER HAD NOT INHERITED $2,500,000 AS OF JULY 27, 2006. IN FACT, WILLARD KNEW THAT THE PERSON FROM WHOM THE CUSTOMER EXPECTED TO RECEIVE THE INHERITANCE, HER RELATIVE, WAS STILL ALIVE. ON OR ABOUT AUGUST 7, 2006, WILLARD RECEIVED AN EMAIL INQUIRY ABOUT THE TRANSACTION FROM A FIELD COMPLIANCE SUPERVISOR AT THE FIRM. IN THE EMAIL, THE SUPERVISOR WROTE THAT HE WAS REVIEWING THE SUITABILITY OF THE TRANSACTION AND REQUESTED AN EXPLANATION FOR THE PURCHASE. WILLARD REPLIED IN AN EMAILED STATING THAT \"THE CLIENT NEEDS A $2 MILLION CONTRACT BECAUSE THEY JUST INHERITED AN ESTATE WORTH $2.5 MILLION WHICH PUTS THEIR TOTAL ESTATE AT APPROXIMATELY $3.1 MILLION.\" WILLARD'S STATEMENT TO THE SUPERVISOR WAS FALSE IN THAT THE CUSTOMER HAD NOT INHERITED AN ESTATE WORTH $2.5 MILLION AS OF AUGUST 7, 2006 AND WILLARD KNEW THAT THE PERSON, FROM WHOM THE CUSTOMER EXPECTED TO RECEIVE THE INHERITANCE, WAS STILL ALIVE. THE FIRM ISSUED THE $2 MILLION VUL POLICY AND WILLARD RECEIVED COMMISSIONS TOTALING APPROXIMATELY $12,034.41 FOR THIS TRANSACTION. ON OR ABOUT FEBRUARY 16, 2007, WILLARD SUBMITTED AN APPLICATION TO THE FIRM TO EFFECT THE PURCHASE OF A $6 MILLION VUL POLICY FOR THE CUSTOMER. IN A COVER LETTER ACCOMPANYING THE APPLICATION, WILLARD WROTE, \"THE PURPOSE OF THE INSURANCE IS TO RECEIVE FUNDS FROM AN INHERITED $2 MILLION FAMILY LIMITED PARTNERSHIP, WHICH SHE IS RECEIVING TAX FREE AND WANTS TO PRESERVE A PORTION OF THOSE FUNDS IN A TAX FREE STATUS FOR HER FAMILY'S FUTURE AND FOR HER HEIRS.\" WILLARD'S STATEMENT IN THE COVER LETTER WAS FALSE IN THAT THE CUSTOMER HAD NOT INHERITED THE $2 MILLION FAMILY LIMITED PARTNERSHIP AS OF FEBRUARY 16, 2007 AND IN FACT, WILLARD KNEW THAT THE PERSON FROM WHOM THE CUSTOMER EXPECTED TO RECEIVE THE INHERITANCE WAS STILL ALIVE. ON OR ABOUT MARCH 27, 2007, THE FIRM ISSUED THE $6 MILLION VUL POLICY AND WILLARD RECEIVED COMMISSIONS TOTALING APPROXIMATELY $38,622.06 FOR THIS TRANSACTION.",
